             sworn. - I am a <rs id="t18040411-44-viclabel254" type="occupation">publican</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18040411-44-victim478 t18040411-44-viclabel254"></join>, I live at <placeName id="t18040411-44-crimeloc255">the Three Tuns, Great New-street, Fetter-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18040411-44-crimeloc255" type="placeName" value="the Three Tuns, Great New-street, Fetter-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18040411-44-crimeloc255" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18040411-44-off252 t18040411-44-crimeloc255"></join>: On the 21st of March, about four o'clock in the afternoon, the prisoner, accompanied by a man and a boy, came into my house and called for a pint of porter, I was in the tap-room when he came in, sitting by the fire in conversation with two of my neighbours; the prisoner sat down at a table nearly opposite me, the person that accompanied him drew near the fire to cover my view of him; after he had sat two or three minutes I perceived, through a vacancy of a person moving, the prisoner take this pot, and putting it off the table, I could perceive he was putting it somewhere about his person; after that, the prisoner, accompanied by this man and a boy, got up; I immediately rose up, and desired a person to follow him that was present, for I had not the least doubt that that man had a pot of mine about him, and in about two or three yards from my own door, I took him by the collar, and charged him with it, he denied it; he wore at that time a large blue apron, I turned up his apron, and in the front of his breeches I found this pot. (The pot produced, and identified by the prosecutor.)</p>
               <p>JAMES - sworn. - I am a barber: On the 21st of March, I went to Mr. Cummings's house to drink a pint of beer, which I usually do, and while I was there, the prisoner at the bar, accompanied with a man and a boy, called for a pint of beer; one man placed himself by the fire, and warmed the beer, I did not perceive him pay for it; in a few minutes they went out of the house; Cummings said to me, I suspect that that man has a pot of mine; he took it from him in the street.</p>

